    "comment": "Rationale: Using a RIBEYE knockout mouse, it is demonstrated that RIBEYE has a role in synaptic vesicle docking. Removal of RIBEYE leads to an more than 50% reduction in the number of docked vesicles (Figure 5). Deficits in synaptic transmission as assessed (Figures 6, 7) are consistent with a reduction in vesicle docking.\n\n10/3/2017 Pim:\n- Experts indicate RIBEYE as the annotated protein. Uniprot lists only 'isoform 2' of the CTBP2 gene as 'ribeye' (http://www.uniprot.org/uniprot/P56546#sequences). This is also mentioned by the authors of the paper: \"To specifically manipulate RIBEYE expression without affecting CtBP2 expression, we focused on the unique 5' A-domain exon of RIBEYE (Fig 1A).\". Annotation is therefore made against CTBP2 isoform 2 specifically.\n-Regulation box is not checked since RIBEYE is believed to mediate the docking itself.. Experimental description: Generation of RIBEYE KI GCamP3 (RBEKI+neo allele)-mutated mice was performed using standard procedures.",
